{"id":53273,"date":"2024-01-23T18:43:12","date_gmt":"2024-01-23T13:13:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=53273"},"modified":"2024-11-06T09:51:27","modified_gmt":"2024-11-06T04:21:27","slug":"master-bedroom-vastu-tips","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/master-bedroom-vastu-tips\/","title":{"rendered":"Master Bedroom Vastu Tips for a Harmonious Living Space."},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Master bedroom vastu at its best! Infuse harmony into your space with expert tips for positive energy, restful sleep, and balanced living.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the symphony of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/\">home design<\/a>, the master bedroom vastu plays a pivotal role as a haven for rest and rejuvenation. We delve into the principles of Vastu, the ancient Indian science of architecture which imparts wisdom on the placement and arrangement of elements to enhance the flow of positive energy. These essential Vastu tips promise to transform your master bedroom into a sanctuary of balance and tranquillity. From the orientation of the bed to the strategic placement of furniture, these insights will guide you in creating a harmonious space that resonates with positive energy.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Master Bedroom Vastu&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Begin with the bed placement. According to Vastu, the head of the bed should ideally be in the south or east direction to promote sound sleep and positive energy flow. Avoid placing the bed under a sloped ceiling or directly in line with the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/modern-bedroom-door-designs-for-home\/\">bedroom door<\/a>. Maintain a sense of equilibrium by incorporating elements in pairs. Whether it&#8217;s bedside tables, lamps, or artwork, symmetrical arrangements create a calming atmosphere. This balance extends to the placement of windows and doors, ensuring a harmonious flow of energy.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183453\/master-bedroom-as-per-vastu.jpg\" alt=\"Align bed head in the south or east direction in the master bedroom as per Vastu to promote sound sleep and positive energy\" class=\"wp-image-53274\" style=\"width:840px;height:504px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183453\/master-bedroom-as-per-vastu.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183453\/master-bedroom-as-per-vastu-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183453\/master-bedroom-as-per-vastu-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183453\/master-bedroom-as-per-vastu-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183453\/master-bedroom-as-per-vastu-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Align your bedroom with cosmic energies<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Design your dream bedroom interiors with 51,040 design possibilities\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/08172515\/design-your-dream-bedroom-interiors-with-51040-design-possibilities.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Master Bedroom Colour as per Vastu<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Opt for soothing and muted colours for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/bedroom-wall-design-ideas\/\">bedroom walls<\/a> to evoke a sense of tranquillity. Earthy tones, soft blues, and gentle greens are believed to enhance relaxation and promote a restful atmosphere. Avoid overly bright or jarring colours in this space. This muted white and pink bedroom flooded with ample natural light is the perfect haven to unwind after a long day.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183502\/master-bedroom-colour-as-per-vastu.jpg\" alt=\"Master bedroom colour, as per Vastu, includes earthy tones, soft blues, and gentle greens for a calming ambience\" class=\"wp-image-53275\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183502\/master-bedroom-colour-as-per-vastu.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183502\/master-bedroom-colour-as-per-vastu-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183502\/master-bedroom-colour-as-per-vastu-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183502\/master-bedroom-colour-as-per-vastu-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183502\/master-bedroom-colour-as-per-vastu-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Add earthy materials &amp; greens to enhance peace<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Master Bedroom Layout as per Vastu&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Ensure that furniture is arranged to facilitate easy movement and a sense of spaciousness. Avoid sharp corners pointing towards the bed, as they are considered inauspicious. Rounded or curved furniture is preferred for a softer energy flow. Layout is also important because clutter disrupts the flow of positive energy. Keep the master bedroom tidy and organised, removing unnecessary items that may hinder the free movement of energy. A clutter-free space contributes to mental peace and clarity.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183509\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu.jpg\" alt=\"Master bedroom layout as per Vastu: Keep the bedroom tidy and clutter-free for positive energy and mental peace\" class=\"wp-image-53276\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183509\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183509\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183509\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183509\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183509\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Mindful bedroom planning reduces stress<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Master Bedroom Vastu for Electronic Gadgets&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Placing too many electronic gadgets, like Television, game boxes, and smart appliances in the bedroom can release negative energy in the bedroom. But since we live in a technology driven world, eliminating all gadgets can be difficult. So reduce as much as you can and instead incorporate elements that resonate positively with you. Artwork, photographs, or symbols that evoke feelings of love, peace, and joy contribute to a harmonious atmosphere.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183523\/master-bedroom-vastu-for-electronic-gadgets.jpg\" alt=\"A harmonious master bedroom per vastu principles: incorporate positive elements, minimise electronics\" class=\"wp-image-53278\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183523\/master-bedroom-vastu-for-electronic-gadgets.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183523\/master-bedroom-vastu-for-electronic-gadgets-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183523\/master-bedroom-vastu-for-electronic-gadgets-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183523\/master-bedroom-vastu-for-electronic-gadgets-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183523\/master-bedroom-vastu-for-electronic-gadgets-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Personal touches make the space uniquely yours<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">North West Master Bedroom Vastu<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>By aligning the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/master-bedroom-design-ideas\/\">master bedroom<\/a> with Vastu principles, you can create a haven that not only promotes physical rest but also nurtures emotional well-being. One such element is mirrors. Mirrors amplify energy, so their placement is crucial. Reflective surfaces should not directly face the bed, as they may disturb sleep. Instead, position mirrors to reflect natural light and open up the space without causing discomfort.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183530\/north-west-master-bedroom-vastu.jpg\" alt=\"Placing mirrors away from the bed in the northwest master bedroom, per Vastu, prevents health problems\" class=\"wp-image-53279\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183530\/north-west-master-bedroom-vastu.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183530\/north-west-master-bedroom-vastu-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183530\/north-west-master-bedroom-vastu-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183530\/north-west-master-bedroom-vastu-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/23183530\/north-west-master-bedroom-vastu-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Place mirrors away from the bed to avoid health issues<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These simple yet profound master bedroom vastu tips can guide the design and arrangement of your space, transforming it into a harmonious space where positive energies converge, and tranquillity prevails. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/contact-us\/\">Consult DesignCafe<\/a> for more insightful design ideas.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you liked reading about Master bedroom vastu tips, also read more about <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu\/\">Master bedroom Layout as per vastu<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FAQs on Master Bedroom Vastu<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. What are the ideal directions for the master bedroom?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The ideal directions for the master bedroom, according to Vastu, are the south or east. Placing the bed with the head towards these directions is believed to promote positive energy flow and enhance restful sleep.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. Is the southeast good for the master bedroom ?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>No, the southeast is generally not considered an ideal direction for the master bedroom in Vastu. It is advised to avoid placing the master bedroom in the southeast, as this direction is associated with the fire element and may disrupt the harmonious energy flow in the sleeping space. Preferred directions for the master bedroom in Vastu are typically south or east.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3. What are some vastu tips for decorating the master bedroom?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Bed Placement:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Position the bed in the south or east direction with the headrest against the south or east wall for positive energy flow and restful sleep.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Balanced Elements:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Maintain symmetry in decor, using pairs of items like bedside tables, lamps, or artwork to create a harmonious atmosphere.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Calming Colours:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Choose soothing colours for bedroom walls, such as earthy tones, soft blues, or gentle greens, to enhance relaxation.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Declutter:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Keep the master bedroom clutter-free to allow the free flow of positive energy and promote mental peace.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Mirror Placement:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Position mirrors thoughtfully, avoiding direct reflection of the bed. Use mirrors to reflect natural light and create a sense of openness.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Furniture Arrangement:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Arrange furniture to facilitate easy movement and avoid sharp corners pointing towards the bed. Opt for rounded or curved furniture.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Ambient Lighting:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Use soft, ambient lighting in the bedroom. Consider dimmers to control light intensity and create a serene environment.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Personalised Elements:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Incorporate personal touches like artwork, photographs, or symbols that evoke positive emotions, making the space uniquely yours.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Avoid Electronics:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Minimise electronic devices in the bedroom, especially near the bed, to promote better sleep and reduce electromagnetic disturbances.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Fresh Air and Ventilation:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Ensure proper ventilation and fresh air circulation in the bedroom for a healthy and positive atmosphere.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember, these Vastu tips serve as general guidelines. Personal preferences and individual circumstances should also be taken into account while decorating the master bedroom.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4. What do Vastu tips for the bedroom say about mirrors?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Vastu, mirrors are considered powerful tools that can influence the energy flow in a space. Avoid placing mirrors directly in front of the bed. The reflection of the bed is believed to disturb sleep and create negative energy.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5. Where should the master bedroom be in a West facing house?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Vastu Shastra, if you have a west-facing house, the ideal location for the master bedroom is typically in the southwest or northwest part of the home. Placing the master bedroom in either of these directions is believed to promote positive energy flow and enhance the well-being of the occupants.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Unwind In Your Personal Sanctuary<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with modular interiors<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"